	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-08-20T07:37:33">Spire Healthcare Group plc is a United Kingdom-based independent hospital group offering a range of integrated surgical, medical and diagnostic services. The Company provides in-patient, daycase and out-patient care from approximately 39 hospitals, around 13 clinics and one specialist care center across England, Wales and Scotland. The Company also owns and operates a sports medicine, physiotherapy and rehabilitation brand, Perform; a screening service, Lifescan, as well as national pathology services. The Company's patients across the United Kingdom consist of private medical insurance (PMI), self-pay and National Health Service (NHS) patients. The Company's primary activities include diagnostics, such as imaging, magnetic resonance imaging or computerized tomography scanning and pathology; out-patient services, such as consulting, treatments, health checks and physiotherapy, and in-patient daycase procedures, such as orthopedics, cardiology, neurology, oncology and general surgery.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-10-14T14:23:18">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Spire Healthcare Group PLC revenues increased 8% to L449.8M. Net income totaled L30.8M vs. loss of L7.8M. Revenues reflect an increase in demand for the Company's products and services due to favorable market conditions. Net Income reflects IE on Capital Financing,Gross decrease from L48.9M (expense) to L0K, Interest on bank facilities decrease of 73% to L6.7M (expense).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
